{"word":"Zebulun","slug":"zebulun","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Zebulun</b> <a href=\"#/H2074\">H2074</a> <br/> 1. Called also Zabulun:<br/> - Son of Jacob and Leah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=30&verse=20'>Gen 30:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=35&verse=23'>Gen 35:23</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=14'>Gen 46:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=13'>Gen 49:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=1&verse=3'>Exo 1:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=2&verse=1'>1Ch 2:1</a> <br/> - Descendants of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=46&verse=14'>Gen 46:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=26&verse=27'>Num 26:27</a> <br/> 2. Tribe of:<br/> - Place of, in march and camp<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=2&verse=3'>Num 2:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=2&verse=7'>Num 2:7</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=10&verse=14'>Num 10:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=10&verse=16'>Num 10:16</a> <br/> - Territory awarded to<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=49&verse=13'>Gen 49:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=19&verse=16'>Jos 19:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=4&verse=13'>Mat 4:13</a> <br/> - Aboriginal inhabitants of the territory of, not expelled<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=1&verse=30'>Jdg 1:30</a> <br/> - Levitical cities of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=21&verse=35'>Jos 21:35</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=77'>1Ch 6:77</a> <br/> - Moses' benediction upon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=33&verse=19'>Deu 33:19</a> <br/> - Loyalty of, in resisting the enemies of Israel:<br/> b With Barak against Sisera<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=4&verse=6'>Jdg 4:6</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=4&verse=10'>Jdg 4:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=5&verse=14'>Jdg 5:14</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=5&verse=18'>Jdg 5:18</a><br/> b With Gideon against the Midianites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=6&verse=35'>Jdg 6:35</a><br/> b With David when made king over Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=12&verse=33'>1Ch 12:33</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=12&verse=40'>1Ch 12:40</a><br/> - Joins with Hezekiah in renewing the Passover<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=30&verse=11'>2Ch 30:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=30&verse=18'>2Ch 30:18</a> <br/> - Conquest of, by Tiglath-Pileser; carried to Assyria into captivity<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=15&verse=29'>2Ki 15:29</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=9&verse=1'>Isa 9:1</a> <br/> - Jesus dwelt in the land of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=4&verse=15'>Mat 4:15</a> <br/> - Twelve thousand sealed<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=66&chapter=7&verse=8'>Rev 7:8</a><br/><a href='S:Israel'>Israel</a> "}]}